sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant FE as browser
    participant GW as api-gateway
    participant AUTH as orches-auth-service
    participant SVC as user-service
    participant DB as user-db
    participant R as Redis

    Note over FE,R: Pre-state: failed_login_attempts = 3   login:softlock not in Redis   hard_locked = false

    rect rgb(240,248,255)
    Note over FE,R: 1. Login & Pre-checks

    FE->>GW: POST /auth/login { email, password }
    GW->>AUTH: login({ email, password })
    AUTH->>SVC: find_user_by_email(email)
    SVC->>DB: SELECT id, is_email_verified, password_hash,<br/>failed_login_attempts, hard_locked<br/>FROM users WHERE email = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
    DB-->>SVC: { failed_login_attempts: 3, hard_locked: false, ... }
    SVC-->>AUTH: user

    alt user not found | not verified | hard_locked = true
        AUTH-->>GW: 401 Unauthorized
        GW-->>FE: 401 Unauthorized
    end

    AUTH->>R: EXISTS login:softlock:{userId}
    R-->>AUTH: 0 (no active soft lock)
    end

    rect rgb(255,248,235)
    Note over FE,R: 2. Credential Validation

    Note over AUTH: bcrypt.compare(password, password_hash) → OK ✓
    end

    rect rgb(240,255,245)
    Note over FE,R: 3. Reset Counter on Password Success

    AUTH->>SVC: reset_login_counter(user_id)
    SVC->>DB: UPDATE users SET failed_login_attempts = 0 WHERE id = ?
    Note right of DB: MFA failures do NOT increment this counter
    DB-->>SVC: updated
    SVC-->>AUTH: OK

    AUTH->>R: DEL login:softlock:{userId}
    Note right of R: Cleanup — safe no-op if key does not exist
    R-->>AUTH: OK

    Note over AUTH: Counter = 0, soft lock cleared. Proceed to MFA or token issuance.
    AUTH-->>GW: 200 → proceed
    GW-->>FE: 200 → proceed
    end
